# A3I local environment. Copy to `.env` (git-ignored) and set your machine's
# paths. The scripts read this file automatically — no `source`/`export`, so a
# fresh shell, IDE task, or cron job works without setup.
#
# Precedence: CLI flag  >  exported env var  >  this .env file  >  the repo
# default shown beside each key. A relative value is taken relative to the repo
# root (so it is independent of your current directory).

# Prepared binary datasets                              (default: data/prepared)
# A3I_PREPARED_ROOT=/mnt/fast/a3i/prepared

# Source Parquet: real-dataset sources + generated synth Parquet  (default: data/raw)
# A3I_PARQUET_DIR=/mnt/fast/a3i/raw

# Experiment result CSVs + runmeta                  (default: experiments/results)
# A3I_RESULTS_ROOT=/mnt/fast/a3i/results

# Generated workload CSVs                         (default: experiments/workloads)
# A3I_WORKLOADS_DIR=experiments/workloads

# Build dir whose tools/ + apps/ hold the executables          (default: build)
# A3I_BUILD_DIR=/home/you/adaptive-aqp-index/build

# Random/sequential bandwidth ratio (0,1] of the device holding the on-disk
# measure columns. The access-path cost model uses it to pick gather vs scan;
# no default, so it must be set for on-disk (capped) runs. Measure it as
# saturated-random / sequential throughput; 1.0 always gathers, in-memory runs
# ignore it. Prefer local benchmark results. Manufacturer read specs imply
# roughly ~0.56 for a Samsung 970 EVO Plus 500GB NVMe SSD and ~0.73 for a
# Samsung 860 EVO 1TB SATA SSD; local results can differ. 
# Local benchmarked values: ~0.39 NVMe (PCIe 3), ~0.81 SATA SSD, ~0.003 HDD.
# A3I_RANDOM_SEQ_BW_RATIO=0.39
